H0.text: Which philosopher, 1872 - 1970, co-wrote 'Principia Mathematica' with A.N. Whitehead. Bertrand Russell

H1.text: Which philosopher, 1872 - 1970, co-wrote 'Principia Mathematica' with A.N. Whitehead. Ludwig Wittgenstein

H2.text: Which philosopher, 1872 - 1970, co-wrote 'Principia Mathematica' with A.N. Whitehead. G.E. Moore

H3.text: Which philosopher, 1872 - 1970, co-wrote 'Principia Mathematica' with A.N. Whitehead. Russellian

A4.text: the three-volume Principia Mathematica, written with Whitehead, was published between 1910 and 1913.

A5.text: Together with his former teacher Alfred North Whitehead, Russell wrote Principia Mathematica, a milestone in the development of classical logic and a major attempt to reduce the whole of mathematics to logic (see logicism).
